comments.body:
Perhaps we could simplify this with a structure that `GENERIC_LT` takes as an argument. Something like

```
struct generic_cmp_data {
     PyArray_CompareFunc *cmp;
     PyArrayObject *arr;
};

NPY_INLINE static int
GENERIC_LT(const char *a, const char *b, const struct generic_compare_data *dat)
{
    return dat->cmp(a, b, dat->arr) < 0;
}
```

The `generic_cmp_data` could be allocated and initialized in the calling function and passed in instead of `cmp` and `arr`.

